        {
          "arguments": {
            "content": "{\n  \"files\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"llvm/llvm-project\",\n      \"path\": \"llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/SelectionDAGISel.cpp\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"llvm/llvm-project\",\n      \"path\": \"llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/SelectionDAGBuilder.cpp\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"llvm/llvm-project\",\n      \"path\": \"llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/ScheduleDAGRRList.cpp\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"llvm/llvm-project\",\n      \"path\": \"llvm/lib/CodeGen/RegAllocGreedy.cpp\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"llvm/llvm-project\",\n      \"path\": \"llvm/lib/CodeGen/MachineFunction.cpp\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"symbols\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"llvm/llvm-project\",\n      \"path\": \"llvm/include/llvm/CodeGen/SelectionDAGISel.h\",\n      \"symbol\": \"SelectionDAGISel\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"llvm/llvm-project\",\n      \"path\": \"llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/SelectionDAGBuilder.h\",\n      \"symbol\": \"SelectionDAGBuilder\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"llvm/llvm-project\",\n      \"path\": \"llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/ScheduleDAGRRList.cpp\",\n      \"symbol\": \"ScheduleDAGRRList\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"llvm/llvm-project\",\n      \"path\": \"llvm/lib/CodeGen/RegAllocGreedy.h\",\n      \"symbol\": \"RAGreedy\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"llvm/llvm-project\",\n      \"path\": \"llvm/include/llvm/CodeGen/MachineFunction.h\",\n      \"symbol\": \"MachineFunction\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"text\": \"The LLVM code generation pipeline consists of five core stages:\\n\\n1. **Instruction Selection (SelectionDAGISel)**: Located at llvm/include/llvm/CodeGen/SelectionDAGISel.h and implemented in llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/SelectionDAGISel.cpp, the SelectionDAGISel class is the common base class for SelectionDAG-based pattern-matching instruction selectors. It translates LLVM IR into target-specific machine code by orchestrating the entire selection process.\\n\\n2. **DAG Building (SelectionDAGBuilder)**: Defined in llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/SelectionDAGBuilder.h and implemented in SelectionDAGBuilder.cpp, the SelectionDAGBuilder class is responsible for translating LLVM IR instructions into SelectionDAG nodes. This is the first step in the DAG-based lowering process where IR operations are converted to target-independent DAG representations.\\n\\n3. **Instruction Scheduling (ScheduleDAGRRList)**: Implemented in llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/ScheduleDAGRRList.cpp, the ScheduleDAGRRList class implements bottom-up and top-down register pressure reduction list scheduling. It schedules DAG nodes to optimize for latency and register pressure using priority-queue-based algorithms.\\n\\n4. **Register Allocation (RAGreedy)**: The RAGreedy class, defined in llvm/lib/CodeGen/RegAllocGreedy.h and implemented in RegAllocGreedy.cpp, implements the greedy register allocator. This pass assigns virtual registers to physical registers and handles spilling when necessary.\\n\\n5. **Machine Function Representation (MachineFunction)**: Defined in llvm/include/llvm/CodeGen/MachineFunction.h and implemented in llvm/lib/CodeGen/MachineFunction.cpp, the MachineFunction class is the machine-level function representation that contains a list of MachineBasicBlocks and manages target-specific function information, register allocation, stack frame information, and other machine-level details.\\n\\nThese components work together in sequence: IR is lowered to DAG nodes by SelectionDAGBuilder, then SelectionDAGISel performs instruction selection to target-specific nodes, the DAG is scheduled by ScheduleDAGRRList to optimize ordering, register allocation is performed by RAGreedy, and the final machine code is represented and managed by MachineFunction.\"\n}\n",
            "file_path": "/workspace/answer.json"
